 fictional vignettes drawn from research findings to illustrate the challenges faced by women working in science today. Additionally, they show how this approach helps make sense of difficult personal experiences and to create a culture of change. Offering a path forward to inclusivity and diversity, this book is crucial reading for anyone working in STEM.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aBusschaert, Nathalie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCaltagirone, Claudia , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDraper, Emily, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHiscock, Jennifer, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aHutchins, Kristin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aK.S. von Krbek, Larissa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKieffer, Marion, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLeigh, David A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcConnell, Anna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRosser, Sue V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlater, Anna, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWatkins, Davita, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311119677040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447362395zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447362395/orig